description: Creates a detector version. The detector version starts in a DRAFT status.

parameters.name: detectorId
parameters.description: The ID of the detector under which you want to create a new version.

parameters.name: externalModelEndpoints
parameters.description: The Amazon Sagemaker model endpoints to include in the detector version. (string) ---

parameters.name: rules
parameters.description: The rules to include in the detector version. (dict) --- A rule. The detector for which the rule is associated. The rule ID. The rule version.

nested_params.name: detectorId
nested_params.description: The detector for which the rule is associated.

parameters.name: modelVersions
parameters.description: The model versions to include in the detector version. (dict) --- The model version. The model ID. The model type. The model version number. arn (string) --- The model version ARN.

parameters.name: ruleExecutionMode
parameters.description: The rule execution mode for the rules included in the detector version. You can define and edit the rule mode at the detector version level, when it is in draft status. If you specify FIRST_MATCHED, Amazon Fraud Detector evaluates rules sequentially, first to last, stopping at the first matched rule. Amazon Fraud dectector then provides the outcomes for that single rule. If you specifiy ALL_MATCHED, Amazon Fraud Detector evaluates all rules and returns the outcomes for all matched rules. The default behavior is FIRST_MATCHED.

parameters.name: tags
parameters.description: A collection of key and value pairs. (dict) --- A key and value pair. A tag key. A value assigned to a tag key.

nested_params.name: value
nested_params.description: A value assigned to a tag key.

nested_items.name: detectorId
nested_items.description: The ID for the created version's parent detector.

nested_items.name: detectorVersionId
nested_items.description: The ID for the created detector.

nested_items.name: status
nested_items.description: The status of the detector version.
